        "introduction": "Surface Codes are one of the most practical quantum error correction methods used to protect quantum information from noise and decoherence. They encode logical qubits using many physical qubits arranged in a 2D lattice. Surface codes are considered one of the most promising approaches for building scalable fault-tolerant quantum computers.",
